### 12.1 Strategy\
\
- **Primary**: Magic link (passwordless email-based authentication)\
- **Future**: Google OAuth, optional password\
- **Senders**: No account required (optional lightweight profile)\
\
### 12.2 Magic Link Flow\
\
```\
User enters email \'e2\'86\'92 System sends magic link email\
    \'e2\'86\'92 User clicks link in email \'e2\'86\'92 Session created\
    \'e2\'86\'92 Redirected to /dashboard\
```\
\
### 12.3 Account Creation\
\
Accounts are created **automatically** during the recipient onboarding flow:\
1. User enters email in Step 1\
2. Email verified via OTP in Step 3a\
3. Payment method added in Step 3b\
4. Account created with verified email + payment method\
5. User lands in dashboard\
\
### 12.4 Session Management\
\
- Use Supabase Auth sessions\
- JWT-based with refresh tokens\
- Session persists across browser sessions (local storage)\
- Protected routes: `/dashboard` requires valid session \'e2\'86\'92 redirect to `/` if not authenticated\
\
### 12.5 Sender "Save My Info"\
\
When a sender checks "Save my information":\
- Create lightweight profile with email + origin address\
- Link to shipments sent through SendMo\
- No password, no full account \'e2\'80\'94 just enough for notifications\
- Can upgrade to full account later\
