## 21. Error Handling & Edge Cases\
\
### 21.1 Address Verification Failures\
\
| Scenario | Handling |\
|----------|---------|\
| Address not found | Show error: "We couldn't verify this address. Please check and try again." |\
| Address partially verified | Show suggested corrections, allow user to accept or re-enter |\
| EasyPost API down | Allow user to proceed with unverified address, flag for manual review |\
\
### 21.2 Payment Failures\
\
| Scenario | Handling |\
|----------|---------|\
| Card declined at activation | Show error, ask to try another card |\
| Capture fails at label generation | Hold shipment, email recipient to update payment, notify sender |\
| Insufficient funds for adjustment | Flag for manual review, email recipient |\
| Stripe API down | Queue for retry, show "Processing payment..." with polling |\
\
### 21.3 Shipping Failures\
\
| Scenario | Handling |\
|----------|---------|\
| No rates available | Show message: "No shipping options available for this package. Check dimensions/weight." |\
| All rates exceed price cap | Show message: "This package exceeds the recipient's shipping budget of $X." |\
| EasyPost label generation fails | Retry up to 3 times, then show error and refund captured payment |\
| Carrier tracking not updating | Show last known status with "Last updated: [time]" |\
\
### 21.4 Link State Edge Cases\
\
| Scenario | Handling |\
|----------|---------|\
| Link deactivated while sender is mid-flow | Show error at rate selection or label purchase |\
| Payment method removed while link is active | Pause link, notify recipient to add new payment method |\
| Multiple senders using link simultaneously | Each gets independent shipment \'e2\'80\'94 link is reusable |\
\
### 21.5 Network / Timeout Errors\
\
- All API calls should have timeouts (30s for external APIs, 10s for internal)\
- Show user-friendly error messages with retry buttons\
- Queue failed webhook processing for retry (exponential backoff)\
